Muthwani MCA George King’ori in Machakos county has protested his brief arrest on Tuesday terming it unlawful and political. King’ori was arrested by Machakos county askaris in Mavoko and  locked up at Athi River police station for close to an hour before the station’s police boss Sharma Wario ordered his release. The arrest  led by Mavoko subcounty inspectorate officer Peter Kingali. Kingali said the MCA was arrested for allegedly leading a mob to disrupt tax collection at a quarry on December 14. The residents were protesting the poor state of roads and drainages . A bridge at Muselele had collapsed after rains pounded the area. The  residents had their leader had earlier toured a quarry to find out how the officers collected taxes.